excerpt: Complex dating to 16th century consisting of a fort, palaces & temple accessed by an arched bridge.
detail_description: Orchha Fort, a stunning architectural gem dating back to the 16th century, is nestled in the picturesque town of Orchha, where the Betwa and Jamni rivers converge. This magnificent complex features an array of palaces, temples, and lush gardens that reflect the exquisite craftsmanship of the Bundela dynasty. Originally built by Rudra Pratap Singh in 1501 AD and later expanded, it showcases a captivating blend of Rajput and Mughal styles.
name: Orchha Fort
address: Ticket counter, fort complex, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

excerpt: Landmark Hindu temple offering a popular destination for pilgrims & daily prayer services.
detail_description: The Shri Ram Raja Mandir is a significant Hindu temple located in Orchha, Madhya Pradesh. It was constructed in the 16th century by Madhukar Shah as a palace for his principal queen Ganesh Kuwari. According to legend, the queen had a dream where Lord Rama instructed her to build a temple for him. The temple is known for its daily prayer services and draws pilgrims from far and wide.
name: Shri Ram Raja Mandir
address: Survey No, 457, Tikamgarh - Jhansi Rd, Marg, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

excerpt: Vast, ornate 16th-century Hindu temple complex with cone-shaped spires & carved stone interiors.
detail_description: Chaturbhuj Temple Orchha is a 16th-century Hindu temple complex with stunning cone-shaped spires and intricately carved stone interiors. It is part of the historical monuments that dot Orchha's rural landscape, including Jehangir Mahal, Raja Mahal, Ram Raja Temple, Laxmi Narayan Temple, and more. The temple was initially constructed to honor Lord Rama but now houses an image of Radha Krishna.
name: Chaturbhuj Temple Orchha
address: 9J2R+22M, Ramraja mandir ke pichhe, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Orchha Sanctuary, established in 1994, is a popular destination for nature enthusiasts and history buffs alike. This wildlife sanctuary offers a serene escape from the historic attractions of Orchha, providing visitors with the opportunity to immerse themselves in nature. Home to diverse wildlife including leopards, tigers, jackals, monkeys, peacocks and over 200 species of birds such as woodpeckers and kingfishers, it's an ideal spot for animal lovers.
name: Orchha Wildlife Sanctuary
address: 8JRR+R95, Lalitpur, Mahrauni Marg, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: The Royal Chhatris, also known as cenotaphs, are a collection of 14 royal tombs located along the picturesque Kanchan Ghat on the banks of River Betwa in Orchha. These historic monuments were constructed in the 17th and 18th centuries to honor the rulers of the Bundela dynasty. The most magnificent among them is Bir Singh Deo's Chhatri, which displays Islamic architectural elements and represents the archaeological brilliance of the Bundelas.
name: The Royal Chhatris
address: Betwa River, beside Kanchana Ghat, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

excerpt: Former royal palace ruins with 16th-century origins, fading murals & ornate stonework.
detail_description: Raja Mahal Orchcha, also known as Raja Mandir, is a historic site that served as the residential quarters for royalty and the administrative center for official business. Built in the 16th century, this former royal palace features fading murals, ornate stonework, and intricate architecture. It was continuously used by successive kings and queens for approximately 150 years before Orchha was abandoned.
name: Raja Mahal Orchcha
address: Raj Mahal Palace, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Laxmi Temple Orchha, also known as Laxmi Narayan Temple, is a stunning architectural marvel that beautifully combines fort and temple styles. Constructed in 1622 by Vir Singh Deo and later reconstructed in 1793 by Prithvi Singh, the temple features exquisite mural paintings depicting mythological themes. The carvings inside the temple showcase scenes from Lord Krishna's life adorned with animal and flower motifs.
name: Laxmi Temple Orchha
address: 9J3J+48H, MP SH 37, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Rai Praveen Mahal is one of the many historical sites in Orchha, a quaint town with a rich cultural heritage. This palace was built by King Indrajit Singh to honor his wife, Raj Praveen, known for her beauty and talents as an artist, dancer, and singer. The palace is renowned for its exquisite architecture and intricate carvings.
name: Rai Praveen Mahal, Orchha
address: 9J2V+MW9, Madhya Pradesh 472001, India

excerpt: 3-story Mughal-style 1600s palace overlooking the Betwa River, featuring 100 rooms & patios.
detail_description: Jahangir Mahal Orchha is a 3-story Mughal-style palace from the 1600s, offering stunning views of the Betwa River and featuring around 100 rooms and patios. It is part of the Orchha Fort Complex, which also includes Raja and Sheesh Mahals. The town of Orchha, located on the banks of the Betwa river, offers nature trails and activities such as rafting.
name: Jahangir Mahal Orchcha
address: 9J2V+8JH, Paryatan Bhawan, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 462003, India

excerpt: Orchha is a town, near the city of Niwari in the Niwari district of Madhya Pradesh state, India. The town was established by a Bundela Rajput ruler Rudra Pratap Singh some time after 1501, as the seat of an eponymous former princely state of covering parts of central & north India, in the Bundelkhand region. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Orchha, located near the city of Niwari in Madhya Pradesh, India, was founded by a Bundela rajput ruler and served as the seat of a former princely state. This town covers parts of central and north India in the Bundelkhand region. While planning a trip to India, Orchha may not have been initially considered compared to popular destinations like New Delhi, Varanasi, and Agra.
name: Orchha
address: Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

name: Rani Laxmi Mahal
address: 9J2Q+CHV, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Nestled within the enchanting Orchha Fort complex, Dauji Ki Kothi stands as a miniature royal palace that captures the essence of a bygone era. Constructed in the 17th century by the merchant class, this architectural gem showcases intricate designs and grand arches that are sure to mesmerize visitors. Although it bears signs of decay, its vast ruins offer an intriguing glimpse into history and serve as a perfect backdrop for photography enthusiasts looking to capture stunning frames.
name: Dauji Ki Kothi
address: 8JXV+MM7, Unnamed Road, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Located on Jhansi road, Orchha Hut Restaurant is a popular spot for lunch, conveniently situated near Laxmi Narayan and Ram Raja. The chef and owner, Mr. Ranu, is well-regarded in the area for his fresh and seasonal dishes. One of their signature dishes is Bundeli Ghosht, a traditional mutton dish cooked slowly in a clay pot with local spices.
name: ORCHHA HUT RESTAURANT
address: LAXMI NARAYAN TEMPLE ROAD, KALYAN COLONY, Orchha Jhansi Rd, behind RAMRAJA TEMPLE, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

name: Krishna Palace Restaurant
address: 9J3R+5F4, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Chaturbhuj Mandir First Floor is a historic temple in Orchha, dedicated to Chaturbhuj, a form of Lord Vishnu. Constructed between 1605 and 1626 by Bir Singh Deo, it stands as a testament to the region's rich cultural heritage. The first floor of the temple offers visitors an opportunity to immerse themselves in the architectural marvels and spiritual significance of this ancient site.
name: Chaturbhuj Mandir First Floor
address: 9J9H+8C2, ramraja street, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Nestled along Orchha Road, Open Sky Restaurant is a delightful gem that offers a unique dining experience with its focus on local cuisine. This charming eatery prides itself on serving fresh vegetables and a limited but thoughtfully curated menu, ensuring every dish bursts with flavor. The ambiance is simply enchanting, as diners can enjoy breathtaking views of the majestic Orchha Fort while savoring their meals.
name: Open Sky Restaurant
address: main road, near Ramraja Temple, in front of PNB Bank, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Sundar Mahal in Orchha is a symbol of unity and love, where two religions coexist peacefully. Built by Durbhajan Singh as a dedication to his lover, this historical site exudes an age-old story of love and sacrifice. The mahal is well-maintained and accessible via the road to Laxmi Narayan temple, attracting both Hindus and Muslims who come to experience its serene vibes.
name: Sundar Mahal
address: 9J2H+PQ7, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

excerpt: Informal restaurant serving cold drinks and a range of international sweets and snack meals.
detail_description: Ramraja restaurant & cafe is a cozy and informal eatery that has been serving delicious food since 1994. Located just before the bridge to the fort in Orchha, it's recommended by Lonely Planet for its inviting ambiance and passion-driven cuisine. The menu offers a variety of international sweets, snack meals, and cold drinks. Visitors rave about the breakfast options available all day, which provide a homely feel at an affordable price.
name: Ramraja restaurant & cafe
address: Ramraja Restaurant Orchha Palace Road, near The Bridge under the monkey biscuit tree, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

detail_description: Shikaragah, located in the Natural Reserve Forest of Orchha, Madhya Pradesh, offers an 8km walking trail through a deep forest. Visitors can explore on foot or rent bicycles for a fee. Situated between two parts of the Betwa river, this isolated territory was once only explored by adventurous few. The area features old temples, a viewpoint by the riverbank, and a concealed shikargaha near a watering hole.
name: Shikaragah, Natural Reserve Forest, Orchha, MP
address: 8MQ5+C2Q, Lidhora, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India

name: Phool Bagh/Palki Mahal
address: 9J2R+M2W, MP SH 37, near Raja Ram Temple, Orchha, Madhya Pradesh 472246, India
